(459, 9, '2017-07-10 22:54:45', '2017-07-10 22:54:45', '<ol>\r\n 	<li style="font-weight: 400"><span style="font-weight: 400">Daily care-giving of residents (All residents including independent residents):</span></li>\r\n</ol>\r\n<ol>\r\n 	<li style="font-weight: 400"><span style="font-weight: 400">Give residents a bath or sponge bath</span></li>\r\n 	<li style="font-weight: 400"><span style="font-weight: 400">Ensure that all residents are cleaned and properly dressed before breakfast.</span></li>\r\n 	<li style="font-weight: 400"><span style="font-weight: 400">Clean and fix the bed by 10:00 AM or earlier.</span></li>\r\n 	<li style="font-weight: 400"><span style="font-weight: 400">Assist in bringing the residents to the dining area to eat, feed the residents, and bring the residents back to the common area or their room.</span></li>\r\n 	<li style="font-weight: 400"><span style="font-weight: 400">Ensure that all residents wear clean clothes at all time. Change the residents clothes if dirty.</span></li>\r\n 	<li style="font-weight: 400"><span style="font-weight: 400">Clean residents hand and face after a meal (for residents who are not capable of doing this). </span></li>\r\n 	<li style="font-weight: 400"><span style="font-weight: 400">Ensure that each resident is well groomed, hair comb, teeth is brushed and nails are trimmed and clean at all times.</span></li>\r\n 	<li style="font-weight: 400"><span style="font-weight: 400">Ensure that residents room is clean, free of dust, organized and not cluttered, furniture are properly arranged.</span></li>\r\n 	<li style="font-weight: 400"><span style="font-weight: 400">All residents personal belonging must be well organized and stowed away at all time.</span></li>\r\n 	<li style="font-weight: 400"><span style="font-weight: 400">Observe any unusual change in behavior, demeanor or appearance. If resident display any symptoms of repeated change in any of the mentioned or the resident has an extreme change, ask the resident if he/she is okay, assess the situation and make corrective action or report to the administrator or call 911 if necessary.</span></li>\r\n 	<li style="font-weight: 400"><span style="font-weight: 400">Adverse change or adverse incident must be documented in the observation log in the residents binder.</span></li>\r\n 	<li style="font-weight: 400"><span style="font-weight: 400">Do not allow resident to sleep in a sofa, chair or wheel chair in the common areas. Ask the resident to go to his/her room to nap or bring the resident to his/her room to nap.</span></li>\r\n 	<li style="font-weight: 400"><span style="font-weight: 400">Make rounds every two (2) hours and document the round. If a resident is unaccounted for 2 hours, observe and initiate Policy and Procedure for Elopement.</span></li>\r\n 	<li style="font-weight: 400"><span style="font-weight: 400">If a resident is unaccounted for observe Policy and Procedure for Elopement immediately.</span></li>\r\n 	<li style="font-weight: 400"><span style="font-weight: 400">Answer the telephone on the 3</span><span style="font-weight: 400">rd</span><span style="font-weight: 400"> ring with proper salutation.</span></li>\r\n 	<li style="font-weight: 400"><span style="font-weight: 400">Assist residents who are checking in by placing all their belongings in the proper location. Move in is not complete until all belongings are put away and medication or scripts are handed to Med-Tech.</span></li>\r\n 	<li style="font-weight: 400"><span style="font-weight: 400">When a resident returns from a rehab or hospital, ensure that he/she is settled back properly in his/her bedroom, all discharge paperwork or 1823 are filed in residents binders and medication script are given to Med-Tech.</span></li>\r\n 	<li style="font-weight: 400"><span style="font-weight: 400">When a resident is leaving the facility, assist family in packing his/her personal belongings and medications.</span></li>\r\n 	<li style="font-weight: 400"><span style="font-weight: 400">Take a few minutes each day to speak to some of the resident or offer to do something for him/her. We are the only contact for most of these people and they need to feel that they are not forgotten and they are loved.</span></li>\r\n</ol>', 'Resident Caregiving', '', 'inherit', 'closed', 'closed', '', '175-revision-v1', '', '', '2017-07-10 22:54:45', '2017-07-10 22:54:45', '', 175, 'http://goodsamalf.com/175-revision-v1/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
