 to the administrator or call 911 if necessary.</span></li>\n 	<li style="font-weight: 400"><span style="font-weight: 400">Adverse change or adverse incident must be documented in the observation log in the residents binder.</span></li>\n 	<li style="font-weight: 400"><span style="font-weight: 400">Make rounds every two (2) hours and document the round. If a resident is unaccounted for 2 hours, observe and initiate Policy and Procedure for Elopement.</span></li>\n 	<li style="font-weight: 400"><span style="font-weight: 400">If a resident is unaccounted for observe Policy and Procedure for Elopement immediately.</span></li>\n 	<li style="font-weight: 400"><span style="font-weight: 400">Answer the telephone on the 3</span><span style="font-weight: 400">rd</span><span style="font-weight: 400"> ring with proper salutation.</span></li>\n 	<li style="font-weight: 400"><span style="font-weight: 400">Assist residents who are checking in by placing all their belongings in the proper location. Move in is not complete until all belongings are put away and medication or scripts are handed to Med-Tech.</span></li>\n 	<li style="font-weight: 400"><span style="font-weight: 400">When a resident returns from a rehab or hospital, ensure that he/she is settled back properly in his/her bedroom, all discharge paperwork or 1823 are filed in residents binders and medication script are given to Med-Tech.</span></li>\n 	<li style="font-weight: 400"><span style="font-weight: 400">When a resident is leaving the facility, assist family in packing his/her personal belongings and medications.</span></li>\n 	<li><span style="font-weight: 400"><span style="font-weight: 400">Take a few minutes each day to speak to some of the resident or offer to do something for him/her. We are the only contact for most of these people and they need to feel that they are not forgotten and they are loved</span></span>\n<ol>\n 	<li style="font-weight: 400"><span style="font-weight: 400">Periodically offer the resident water or something to drink to avoid dehydration. Most resident forget to do this and they end up being ill.</span></li>\n 	<li style="font-weight: 400"><span style="font-weight: 400">Check if resident is wet or dirty every 2 hours. Clean resident with paper towel or wipes. DO NOT USE FACE TOWEL.</span></li>\n 	<li style="font-weight: 400"><span style="font-weight: 400">Check on resident who are not mobile or are ill every hour to find out if he/she need something or if condition has regressed or improved.</span></li>\n 	<li style="font-weight: 400"><span style="font-weight: 400">All incidents, minor and major must be logged in the residents log book and in caregivers log book.</span></li>\n 	<li style="font-weight: 400"><span style="font-weight: 400">Do laundry. Fold and deliver to resident. </span></li>\n 	<li style="font-weight: 400"><span style="font-weight: 400">Turn off TV, fans, or lights that are not being used including TV in residents room.</span></li>\n 	<li style="font-weight: 400"><span style="font-weight: 400">Caregivers will be assigned to a certain part of the facility daily. That care giver will be accountable for the condition of that unit and of the residents in that unit.</span></li>\n 	<li style="font-weight: 400"><span style="font-weight: 400">Caregivers must be visible in the area at all times to assist all the residents.</span></li>\n 	<li style="font-weight: 400"><span style="font-weight: 400">Caregivers must sanitized their hands after handling a third resident.</span></li>\n 	<li style="font-weight: 400"><span style="font-weight: 400">Each caregiver is mandated to take One (1) hour of his/her time to conduct an activity with the residents either in the morning or in the afternoon. Log your name in the activity log book. Caregivers must take turn doing activity with residents.</span></li>\n 	<li style="font-weight: 400"><span style="font-weight: 400">Check appointment board daily. Afternoon caregiver copy of the residents face sheet and 